## Step 3 — Output the diagram

### Always show in chat
Display the complete mermaid code block in the chat response.

### Offer to write to a doc file
After showing the diagram, suggest writing it to the appropriate location:

| Diagram subject | Target location |
|----------------|-----------------|
| Workflow execution flow | `doc/workflows/core/<resource>-workflows.md` or `doc/workflows/<category>/` |
| Design/architecture | `doc/architecture/designs/` |
| Data model | `doc/architecture/` or existing design doc |
| Standalone reference | New file in `doc/architecture/` |

If the target file already exists, **append** the diagram under a new section heading. If it doesn't exist, create a new markdown file with a title, brief description, and the diagram.

### Image export reminder
After writing to a doc file, mention:

> To render this diagram as SVG, run:
> ```bash
> python scripts/export_mermaid_images.py --input <path-to-markdown-file>
> ```
> Output will be in `doc/images/mermaid/`.

